         <div>
            <head>"DREAM VARIATION"</head>
            <lg>
               <l>To fling my arms wide 7</l>
               <l>In some place of the sun,</l>
               <l>To whirl and to dance</l>
               <l>Till the bright day is done.</l>
               <l>Then rest at cool evening</l>
               <l>Beneath a tall tree</l>
               <l>While night comes gently</l>
               <l>Dark like me.</l>
               <l>That is my dream.</l>
               <l>To fling my arms wide</l>
               <l>In the face of the sun.</l>
               <l>Dance! Whirl! Whirl!</l>
               <l>Till the quick day is done.</l>
               <l>Rest at pale evening,</l>
               <l>A tall, slim tree,</l>
               <l>Night coming tenderly</l>
               <l>Black like me.</l>
            </lg>
            <byline>-Langston Hughes</byline>
         </div>
